{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2024-2088","published":"2024-09-06T11:09:01Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:20:45.576496Z","upstream":["CVE-2024-7347"],"summary":"nginx security update","details":"NGINX is a free, open-source, high-performance HTTP server and reverse proxy,  as well as an IMAP/POP3 proxy server.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nNGINX Open Source and NGINX Plus have a vulnerability in the ngx_http_mp4_module, which might allow an attacker to over-read NGINX worker memory resulting in its termination, using a specially crafted mp4 file. The issue only affects NGINX if it is built with the ngx_http_mp4_module and the mp4 directive is used in the configuration file. Additionally, the attack is possible only if an attacker can trigger the processing of a specially crafted mp4 file with the ngx_http_mp4_module.Â  Note: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.(CVE-2024-7347)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"nginx","ecosystem":"openEuler:24.03-LTS","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/nginx&distro=openEuler-24.03-LTS"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"1.24.0-2.oe2403"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["nginx-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-debuginfo-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-debugsource-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-mod-devel-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-mod-http-image-filter-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-mod-http-perl-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-mod-http-xslt-filter-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-mod-mail-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm","nginx-mod-stream-1.24.0-2.oe2403.aarch64.rpm"],"noarch":["nginx-all-modules-1.24.0-2.oe2403.noarch.rpm","nginx-filesystem-1.24.0-2.oe2403.noarch.rpm","nginx-help-1.24.0-2.oe2403.noarch.rpm"],"src":["nginx-1.24.0-2.oe2403.src.rpm"],"x86_64":["nginx-1.24.0-2.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","nginx-debuginfo-1.24.0-2.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","nginx-debugsource-1.24.0-2.oe2403.x86_64.rpm","nginx-mod-devel-1.24.0-2.oe2403.x86_64.rp